{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":79010,"duration_api_ms":67492,"num_turns":8,"result":"All validation passes. Here is the ExecutionPayload:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Addressed all 4 pending amendments. (1) Added tracing::warn! to unique_terminal_replay_match (fs.rs:2832-2837) when requested_run_id is Some but requested_started_at is None, making the contract violation diagnosable in production logs before returning None. (2) Added merge_attempt_entries_fills_all_optional_fields round-trip coverage test to model.rs — constructs a primary with all optional fields None and a secondary with all fields populated, merges, asserts every optional field is filled from secondary; then verifies existing non-None values on primary are NOT overwritten by secondary. (3) Removed new-row auto-population of plan_hash from snapshot in record_task_run_start (fs.rs:3039): effective_plan_hash now uses only plan_hash.map(str::to_owned), never falling back to the snapshot. snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation still records the snapshot hash for provenance, enabling safe_plan_hash_backfill during later finalization when the plan hasn't evolved. (4) Replaced the None-provenance backfill branch in safe_plan_hash_backfill (fs.rs:2608-2616) with an unconditional return false — legacy entries with snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=None are no longer silently relabeled with the current snapshot hash, since None is ambiguous between 'created before any plan' and 'created by older code version'. Updated 5 existing tests whose assertions relied on removed auto-population or None-provenance backfill behavior.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes but will appear in cargo fmt --check across the full workspace.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 1: Added tracing::warn! log to unique_terminal_replay_match (fs.rs:2832-2837) before the return None when requested_run_id is Some but requested_started_at is None. The warning message identifies the specific contract violation so operators can diagnose it in production logs.\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 2: Added merge_attempt_entries_fills_all_optional_fields test to model.rs. Constructs a primary with all optional fields None (run_id, plan_hash, snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation, outcome_detail, finished_at) and a secondary with all populated. Asserts merge fills every optional field from secondary and started_at takes the minimum. Second phase constructs a primary with all fields populated and verifies merge does NOT overwrite existing values.\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 3: Changed effective_plan_hash in record_task_run_start (fs.rs:3039) from plan_hash.map(str::to_owned).or_else(|| current_snapshot_hash.clone()) to plan_hash.map(str::to_owned). The snapshot hash is still read and recorded in snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation for provenance but is no longer used to auto-populate plan_hash on new rows, eliminating the persist_plan race condition.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 4: Replaced the None-provenance branch in safe_plan_hash_backfill (fs.rs:2608-2616) — previously populated both snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation and plan_hash from the current snapshot — with an unconditional return false. Added explanatory comment documenting that None is ambiguous between pre-plan and legacy code origins, so backfilling would risk silently relabeling legacy entries.\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot test (service.rs:4764-4783): post-start assertion changed from Some(expected_plan_hash) to None (no auto-population on new rows), ad